net.dempsy.config

Class Node

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.dempsy.config.Node

  • public class Node
extends Object

    In Dempsy parlance, a Node is the intersection of a Cluster with physical compute resources. Typically, a process space on a machine will have a single Node for a given Cluster. That's NOT to say the process space will have a single Node. Only that (typically*) you wont have multiple Nodes from the same Cluster in the same process space.

    * In some rarse cases (for example, when unit testing) you can have multiple Nodes from the same Cluster in a single process space. However, in a real deployment this doesn't make much sense.

    The Node class is really a "Builder" that provides for the easy configuration of a distributed Cluster.

    Please see the User Guide for more information.
